'''安德鲁·R·惠勒'''（{{lang-en|Andrew R. Wheeler}}，{{bd|1964年|12月23日||}}），美国律师，第15任[[美国国家环境保护局|美国国家环境保护局]]局长<ref name="Administrator">{{cite web |title=EPA's Administrator |url=https://www.epa.gov/aboutepa/epas-administrator |website=EPA |access-date=2020-08-19 |archive-date=2021-01-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210113000026/https://www.epa.gov/aboutepa/epas-administrator |dead-url=no }}</ref>，曾于2018年4月至7月任环保局副局长<ref>{{Cite web |last=U.S. Environmental Protection Agency |title=EPA's Deputy Administrator |url=https://www.epa.gov/aboutepa/epas-deputy-administrator |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622034527/https://www.epa.gov/aboutepa/epas-deputy-administrator |access-date=2018-04-23 |archive-date=2018-06-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，2018年7月至2019年2月任代局长；同时任职于{{tsl|en|Faegre Baker Daniels|费格·贝克·丹尼尔斯}}律师事务所，为煤炭大亨{{tsl|en|Robert E. Murray|罗伯特·E·穆勒}}的代表律师，也从事反对奥巴马政府保护法规的游说工作<ref name=":2">{{Cite news |last=Wolff |first=Eric |date=2018-05-05 |title=Pruitt's replacement 'should scare anyone who breathes' |work=Politico |type=updated July 5, 2018 |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/05/05/scott-pruitt-epa-andrew-wheeler-570641 |access-date=2018-07-05 |archive-date=2019-08-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816185529/https://www.politico.com/story/2018/05/05/scott-pruitt-epa-andrew-wheeler-570641 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

惠勒[[全球暖化否定说|否定气候变化]]<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |last=Mufson |first=Steven |date=2018-07-05 |title=Scott Pruitt's likely successor has long lobbying history on issues before the EPA |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/economy/epas-acting-administrator-has-long-lobbying-record-on-issues-before-the-agency/2018/07/05/a591cd40-6a6b-11e8-bea7-c8eb28bc52b1_story.html |access-date=2018-07-05 |website=Washington Post |language=en |archive-date=2020-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029091520/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/economy/epas-acting-administrator-has-long-lobbying-record-on-issues-before-the-agency/2018/07/05/a591cd40-6a6b-11e8-bea7-c8eb28bc52b1_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，一直批评政府限制{{tsl|en|Greenhouse gas emissions by the United States|美国温室气体排放|温室气体排放}}和成立[[政府間氣候變化專門委員會|政府間氣候變化專門委員會]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=Farrick |first=Ryan J. |date=2017-07-26 |title=Trump Nominates Coal Industry Lobbyist Andrew Wheeler To Help Run EPA |url=http://www.legalreader.com/trump-nominates-coal-industry-lobbyist-andrew-wheeler-help-run-epa/ |access-date=2017-08-25 |publisher=Legal Reader |archive-date=2018-07-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706103835/https://www.legalreader.com/trump-nominates-coal-industry-lobbyist-andrew-wheeler-help-run-epa/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，因而成为{{tsl|en|United States Senate Committee on Environment and Public Works|美国参议院环境与公共工程委员会}}及委员会主席、参议员[[吉姆·英霍夫|吉姆·英霍夫]]的首席顾问律师<ref name=":3" />。

2017年10月，惠勒获总统[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]提名为国家环保局副局长<ref name="nyt171005">{{Cite news |last=Friedman |first=Lisa |date=2017-10-05 |title=Trump Nominates a Coal Lobbyist to Be No. 2 at E.P.A. |work=New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/05/climate/trump-epa-andrew-wheeler.html |access-date=2017-10-06 |archive-date=2020-12-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215011404/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/05/climate/trump-epa-andrew-wheeler.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，2018年1月再获提名<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=PN1084 — Andrew Wheeler — Environmental Protection Agency (115th Congress, 2017-2018) |url=https://www.congress.gov/nomination/115th-congress/1084 |access-date=2018-01-29 |publisher=U.S. Senate |archive-date=2020-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305163852/https://www.congress.gov/nomination/115th-congress/1084 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，同年4月获参议院确认<ref name=":1">{{Cite news |last1=Grandoni |first1=Dino |last2=Dennis |first2=Brady |date=2018-04-12 |title=Senate confirms a former coal lobbyist as Scott Pruitt's second-in-command at EPA |work=Washington Post |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/economy/the-senate-is-about-to-confirm-a-coal-lobbyist-as-top-epa-deputy/2018/04/12/b1bb6844-3dbe-11e8-a7d1-e4efec6389f0 |access-date=2018-04-13 |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115162807/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/economy/the-senate-is-about-to-confirm-a-coal-lobbyist-as-top-epa-deputy/2018/04/12/b1bb6844-3dbe-11e8-a7d1-e4efec6389f0_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2018年7月9日，由于[[史考特·普魯特|史考特·普魯特]]辞职，惠勒代理其局长职务<ref name="globe2018">{{Cite news |date=2018-07-05 |title=Scott Pruitt resigns as EPA head |work=Boston Globe |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/news/politics/2018/07/05/scott-pruitt-resigns-epa-head/emLwyNeWitltYlLG9T10XO/story.html |access-date=2018-07-05 |archive-date=2021-01-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115162810/https://www.bostonglobe.com/news/politics/2018/07/05/scott-pruitt-resigns-epa-head/emLwyNeWitltYlLG9T10XO/story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Friedman |first=Lisa |date=2018-11-16 |title=Trump Says He'll Nominate Andrew Wheeler to Head the E.P.A. |language=en |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/16/climate/trump-andrew-wheeler-epa.html |accessdate=2021-01-15 |archive-date=2020-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201121144140/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/16/climate/trump-andrew-wheeler-epa.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2019年2月28日，参议院以52比47分比数确认其提名<ref name=":5">{{Cite news |last=Daly |first=Matthew |date=2019-02-28 |title=Senate confirms acting EPA chief for permanent role |language=en |work=Associated Press |url=https://www.apnews.com/83a03cf65439434da94d15088056f8a2 |access-date=2019-02-28 |archive-date=2019-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190228184541/https://apnews.com/83a03cf65439434da94d15088056f8a2 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==早年经历及教育==
1964年12月23日，惠勒在[[美国|美国]][[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]][[汉密尔顿_(俄亥俄州)|汉密尔顿]]出生，曾是[[鹰级童军|鹰级童军]]<ref name="Administrator"/>；1987年获[[克里夫兰|克里夫兰]][[凱斯西儲大學|凱斯西儲大學]][[文学士|文学士]]学位（主修英语和生物）<ref>{{Cite web |title=Case Western Reserve University Alumni Graduates of 1987 |url=http://alumnius.net/case_western_reserve-9092-year-1987-page2#alumni |access-date=2017-08-25 |publisher=Case Western Reserve University |archive-date=2020-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305171848/https://alumnius.net/case_western_reserve-9092-year-1987-page2#alumni |dead-url=no }}</ref>，1990年获[[圣路易斯华盛顿大学|圣路易斯华盛顿大学]]法学院[[法律博士|法律博士]]学位<ref>{{Cite web |date=2009 |title=Class Notes 1990 |url=https://law.wustl.edu/magazine/spring2009/ClassNotes.pdf |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120914112547/http://law.wustl.edu/magazine/spring2009/ClassNotes.pdf |archive-date=2012-09-14 |access-date=2017-08-25 |publisher=Washington university law magazine }}</ref>，1998年完成[[乔治梅森大学|乔治梅森大学]][[工商管理硕士|工商管理硕士]]课程<ref name="Almanac" />。

==职业生涯==
===环保局早期===
惠勒的首份工作，是于1991年至1995年间担任国家环境保护局污染防治与毒理学办公室（Office of Pollution Prevention and Toxics）信息管理科（Information Management Division）主任特别助理<ref name="Almanac">{{Cite book |last=Friedman |first=Lisa |url=https://archive.org/details/almanacofunelect0000unse/page/614 |title=The Almanac of the Unelected: Staff of the U.S. Congress |date=2008 |publisher=Bernan Press |isbn=978-1598881844 |page=[https://archive.org/details/almanacofunelect0000unse/page/614 614] |registration=yes}}</ref>，处理[[毒性|有毒化学品]]、{{tsl|en|pollution prevention|污染防治}}和[[知情权|知情权]]问题。1993年，惠勒获局颁发的铜奖章，1994年再度荣膺该殊荣<ref name="Baker Daniels">{{Cite web |title=Andrew R. Wheeler |url=https://www.faegrebd.com/andrew-wheeler |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171105173211/https://www.faegrebd.com/andrew-wheeler |archive-date=2017-11-05 |access-date=2017-08-25 |publisher=Faegre Baker Daniels }}</ref>。

===参议院职员===
1995年1月至1997年1月，惠勒担任参议员[[吉姆·英霍夫|吉姆·英霍夫]]的首席顾问律师<ref name=":2" />。1997年，惠勒加入英霍夫任主席的美国参议院清洁空气、气候变暖、湿地和核安全小组委员会（US Senate Subcommittee on Clean Air, Climate Change, Wetlands, and Nuclear Safety），担任多数党幕僚长，至2001年，是他首度供职于国会；此后又于2001年至2003年间出任小组委员会主席[[喬治·沃伊諾維奇|喬治·沃伊諾維奇]]的少数党幕僚长，2003年至2009年任{{tsl|en|United States Senate Committee on Environment and Public Works|美国参议院环境与公共工程委员会}}首席顾问律师<ref name="nyt171005" />。在此期间，惠勒多数时间是在寻求政府减少对排放温室气体行业的限制<ref name=":4">{{Cite news |title=Get To Know Andrew Wheeler, Ex-Coal Lobbyist With Inside Track To Lead EPA |language=en |work=NPR.org |url=https://www.npr.org/2018/07/06/626525274/get-to-know-andrew-wheeler-ex-coal-lobbyist-with-inside-track-to-lead-epa |access-date=2018-07-07 |archive-date=2020-12-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201217004421/https://www.npr.org/2018/07/06/626525274/get-to-know-andrew-wheeler-ex-coal-lobbyist-with-inside-track-to-lead-epa |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而参议员英霍夫则以[[全球暖化否定说|否认气候变化]]的立场著称，有一次曾经[[雪球|雪球]]带入国会，以此证明气候变化不存在<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":3" />。

2005年，惠勒被《{{tsl|en|National Journal|国家期刊}}》列入国会最佳幕僚长（Top Congressional Staff Leaders）名单，并获[[第106届美国国会|第106届国会]]{{tsl|en|John C. Stennis|约翰·斯坦尼斯}}国会职员奖<ref name="Baker Daniels" />。

===说客===
2009年至2017年，惠勒担任{{tsl|en|Faegre Baker Daniels|费格·贝克·丹尼尔斯}}律师事务所能源及自然资源问题说客<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-03-16 |title=Sources:Trump expected to tap Wheeler as EPA deputy |url=http://www.politico.com/story/2017/03/andrew-wheeler-epa-deputy-sources-236151 |access-date=2017-08-25 |publisher=Politico |archive-date=2020-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125024813/https://www.politico.com/story/2017/03/andrew-wheeler-epa-deputy-sources-236151 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrew-wheeler-95892412/Starting |title=Andrew Wheeler |access-date=2018-07-13 |website=Linked in profile |quote=Andrew's unique position and broad expertise in domestic and international public policy has helped him develop a highly specialized view of how to execute effective advocacy programs before the U.S. Congress and the Executive Branch involving all aspects of energy and environmental policy. His knowledge and insider understanding of the Senate, House and various federal agencies allows Andrew to develop tailored, comprehensive strategies that assist clients in realizing their federal affairs goals and build lasting relationships with key policymakers |archive-date=2021-04-04 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20210404155855/https://www.linkedin.com/in/andrew-wheeler-95892412/Starting }}</ref>。自2009年起，惠勒担任煤炭大亨{{tsl|en|Robert E. Murray|罗伯特·E·穆勒}}公司穆勒能源（Murray Energy）的代表律师<ref>{{Cite news |date=2017-03-16 |title=Trump to name coal lobbyist as deputy EPA chief: report |work=The Hill |url=http://thehill.com/blogs/blog-briefing-room/news/324418-trump-to-name-coal-lobbyist-as-deputy-epa-chief-report |access-date=2017-08-25 |archive-date=2020-11-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201101081808/http://thehill.com/blogs/blog-briefing-room/news/324418-trump-to-name-coal-lobbyist-as-deputy-epa-chief-report |dead-url=no }}</ref>，穆勒是[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]总统的坚定支持者<ref name="lobbyist">{{Cite news |date=2017-09-29 |title=Trump to tap longtime coal lobbyist for EPA's No. 2 spot |work=The Washington Post |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/energy-environment/wp/2017/07/21/trump-to-tap-longtime-coal-lobbyist-for-epas-number-two-spot/ |access-date=2017-08-25 |archive-date=2020-11-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201117020750/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/energy-environment/wp/2017/07/21/trump-to-tap-longtime-coal-lobbyist-for-epas-number-two-spot/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。穆勒能源是惠勒酬金最高的客户，金额至少达30万美元<ref name=":3" />，最高可达330万美元<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-01-10 |title=Lobbying Disclosure Act Database |url=https://soprweb.senate.gov/index.cfm?event=processSearchCriteria |website=Lobbying Disclosure Act Database |accessdate=2021-01-15 |archive-date=2021-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210104095542/https://soprweb.senate.gov/index.cfm?event=processSearchCriteria |dead-url=no }}</ref>。惠勒也从事反对奥巴马政府为发电厂制定气候法规，试图说服能源部补贴煤炭厂的游说工作<ref name=":2" />。2017年3月，在惠勒的组织下，穆勒和[[美国能源部长|能源部长]][[里克·佩里|里克·佩里]]举行会谈；会后，穆勒提倡收回环境法规，煤炭行业提供保护<ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Friedman |first=Lisa |date=2017-10-05 |title=Trump Nominates a Coal Lobbyist to Be No. 2 at E.P.A. |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/05/climate/trump-epa-andrew-wheeler.html |access-date=2018-02-06 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2020-12-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215011404/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/05/climate/trump-epa-andrew-wheeler.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===环保局副局长===
2017年10月，惠勒获总统特朗普提名为[[美国国家环境保护局|美国国家环境保护局]]副局长<ref name="nyt171005" />。然而，由于参议院于2017年底休会<ref name=":0" />，他的提名于2018年1月3日被退回到白宫。2018年4月12日，特朗普再度递交提名，这一次，[[乔·曼钦|乔·曼钦]]、[[海迪·海特坎普|海迪·海特坎普]]和[[喬·唐納利|喬·唐納利]]三名民主党议员发起大体上遵循党派路线的投票，最终以53比45的比数。，确认了他的提名<ref name=":1" />。

自宣誓就任之日起，惠勒就和他担任说客时期的客户，举行了至少三场会晤，这可能会违反特朗普政府的道德承诺，以及惠勒之前在提名确认听证会上所做承诺.<ref>{{Cite web |title=EPA: Despite his assurances, Wheeler met with former clients |url=https://www.eenews.net/stories/1060091287 |access-date=2018-07-26 |website=www.eenews.net |language=en |archive-date=2020-12-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201203085340/https://www.eenews.net/stories/1060091287 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。环保局道德官员贾斯蒂娜·富（Justina Fugh）表示惠勒的做法不违反政府道德承诺，因为惠勒加入环保局的两年前就没有替他们工作<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cama |first=Timothy |date=2018-07-27 |title=EPA ethics official defends Wheeler over meetings |url=https://thehill.com/policy/energy-environment/399177-epa-ethics-official-defends-wheeler-over-meetings |access-date=2019-03-13 |website=TheHill |language=en |archive-date=2020-12-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215091839/https://thehill.com/policy/energy-environment/399177-epa-ethics-official-defends-wheeler-over-meetings |dead-url=no }}</ref>。佛蒙特州参议员[[伯尼·桑德斯|伯尼·桑德斯]]“强烈反对”惠勒在未来接任普鲁特<ref>{{Cite news |last=Geng |first=Annie |date=2018-07-05 |title=Senator Bernie Sanders: Pruitt's replacement is just as bad on the environment |work=CNN |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/07/05/politics/sanders-republican-wheeler-cnntv/index.html |accessdate=2021-01-15 |archive-date=2018-12-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181210170807/https://www.cnn.com/2018/07/05/politics/sanders-republican-wheeler-cnntv/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===环保局代局长===
2018年7月5日，[[史考特·普魯特|史考特·普魯特]]宣布辞职，7月6日生效，惠勒将代理局长职务<ref name="globe2018" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Cama |first=Timothy |date=2018-07-15 |title=EPA chief draws sharp contrast to Pruitt |work=The Hill |url=http://thehill.com/policy/energy-environment/396985-new-epa-chief-draws-sharp-contrast-to-pruitt |accessdate=2021-01-15 |archive-date=2020-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206070252/https://thehill.com/policy/energy-environment/396985-new-epa-chief-draws-sharp-contrast-to-pruitt |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2018年10月14日，《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》发表[[社论|社论]]，批评惠勒的提案贬低减少空气污染对公众健康带来的好处，指其专门针对2011年一项发现，即奥巴马政府将其视作控制特定污染物的情报资产<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-10-14 |title=Editorial: Environmental Protection Racket |page=8 |work=The New York Times}}</ref>。2018年11月16日，惠勒代理局长仅五个月，获提名环保局局长<ref>{{Cite news |last=Knickmeyer |first=Ellen |date=2018-11-16 |title=Trump says he'll name Andrew Wheeler Permanent Head of EPA |work=Time |url=http://time.com/5457526/trump-wheeler-epa-head-permanent |via=Associated Press |accessdate=2021-01-15 |archive-date=2018-11-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181118010210/http://time.com/5457526/trump-wheeler-epa-head-permanent/ |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

2018年，特朗普政府发表调查气候变暖对美国影响的《国家气候评估》（National Climate Assessment）报告，这项调查自奥巴马政府开始，已延续数年。然而，这份报告遭到惠勒治下环保局驳回。环保局错误声称奥巴马政府向报告作者施压，要求侧重写最坏的情况。环保局解释缘由时引用了福斯新闻评论家塔克·卡尔森（Tucker Carlson）成立保守主义网站“每日来电”（''Daily Caller''）的一篇报道。事实核查网站认为，每日来电的报道未列出具体证据，评估报道有提及最好和最坏情况，且大部分内容都在探讨眼下的气候变暖影响。事实核查网站指出，报告经过多番内部和外部的审查，也面向公众审查三个月。对此，每日来电援引一份备忘录，证明所谓的奥巴马政府向报告作者施压，但被是时差和网站反驳<ref>{{Cite web |last=McDonald |first=Jessica |date=2018-12-26 |title=Trump Administration Distorts the Facts On Climate Report |url=https://www.factcheck.org/2018/12/trump-administration-distorts-the-facts-on-climate-report/ |access-date=2019-06-11 |website=FactCheck.org |language=en-US |archive-date=2019-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190106111258/https://www.factcheck.org/2018/12/trump-administration-distorts-the-facts-on-climate-report/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2018年11月，惠勒被要求说出环保局三个用于洁净空气的政策。他迟疑许久，说出了三个答案，其中两个是奥巴马政府遏制污染政策的[[推回|推回]]政策<ref>{{Cite news |last=Gregory Wallace |title=Acting EPA administrator says administration deserves credit for decline in carbon emissions in wake of climate report |publisher=CNN |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/11/28/politics/epa-administrator-climate-report/index.html |access-date=2018-11-28 |archive-date=2020-11-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201126131902/https://edition.cnn.com/2018/11/28/politics/epa-administrator-climate-report/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===环保局局长===
[[File:EPA_Administrator_Wheeler_at_the_White_House_State_Leadership_Day_(48714392221)_(cropped).jpg|thumb]]
2019年2月，参议院用大体上遵循党派路线的投票，以52比47的结果确认惠勒担任环保局局长的提名<ref name=":5" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Roll Call Vote #33: Question: On the Nomination (Confirmation Andrew Wheeler, of Virginia, to be Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency |url=https://www.senate.gov/legislative/LIS/roll_call_lists/roll_call_vote_cfm.cfm?congress=116&session=1&vote=00033 |website=United States Senate, 116th Congress (1st Session |accessdate=2021-01-15 |archive-date=2019-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308081749/https://www.senate.gov/legislative/LIS/roll_call_lists/roll_call_vote_cfm.cfm?congress=116&session=1&vote=00033 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2019年，惠勒赞同环保局一项拟议中的规定，禁止该部门在调查时利用不公开的原始数据<ref name="Lavelle">{{Cite web |last=Lavelle |first=Marianne |date=2019-06-06 |title=EPA Science Advisers Push Back on Wheeler, Say He's Minimizing Their Role |url=https://insideclimatenews.org/news/05062019/epa-wheeler-science-advisory-board-meeting-limiting-scientific-studies-trump-methane-rule |website=InsideClimate News |accessdate=2021-01-15 |archive-date=2020-11-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107231445/https://insideclimatenews.org/news/05062019/epa-wheeler-science-advisory-board-meeting-limiting-scientific-studies-trump-methane-rule |dead-url=no }}</ref>。该规定由惠勒的前任斯科特·普鲁特提出<ref name="Meyer" />。惠勒将该提议定为“透明度”规则；科学家反对该规定，认为这会严重限制国家环保局的研究，因为这些研究不会公开个人及机密数据<ref name="Lavelle" /><ref name="Meyer">{{Cite news |last=Meyer |first=Robinson |date=2018-07-17 |title=Even Geologists Hate the EPA's New Science Rule |work=The Atlantic |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2018/07/scott-pruitts-secret-science-rule-could-still-become-law/565325 |accessdate=2021-01-15 |archive-date=2020-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125032442/https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2018/07/scott-pruitts-secret-science-rule-could-still-become-law/565325/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。该提议也会阻止环保局利用许多重要研究支撑各项法规，包括[[空气污染|空气污染]]的法规<ref name="Lavelle" />。69名科学家和医学团体反对该提议，包括[[美国肺脏协会|美国肺脏协会]]、[[美国医学会|美国医学会]]和[[美国心理学会|美国心理学会]]，以及五大顶尖科学期刊《[[科学_(期刊)|科学]]》、《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》、《[[细胞_(期刊)|细胞]]》、《[[PLOS_ONE|PLOS ONE]]》和《[[美国国家科学院院刊|美国国家科学院院刊]]》的编者<ref name="Meyer" />。前环保局局长组成的两党团体在接受{{tsl|en|United States House Energy Subcommittee on Oversight and Investigations|美国众议院能源监督与调查小组委员会|众议院能源监督与调查小组委员会}}质询时，也批评该提议限制科学在环保局制定政策时所起的作用<ref name="pullano">{{Cite news |last=Pullano |first=Nina |date=2019-06-11 |title=3 Republican ex-EPA Chiefs Rebuke Trump EPA on Climate Policy & Science |work=Inside Climate News |url=https://insideclimatenews.org/news/11062019/epa-climate-change-anti-science-rebuke-gop-former-administrators-thomas-whitman-reilly-mccarthy |accessdate=2021-01-15 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108014556/https://insideclimatenews.org/news/11062019/epa-climate-change-anti-science-rebuke-gop-former-administrators-thomas-whitman-reilly-mccarthy |dead-url=no }}</ref>。环保局的科学顾问委员会也反对该提议<ref name="Lavelle" />。

惠勒同意该提案，他呼吁环保局参照[[美国食品药品监督管理局|美国食品药品监督管理局]]，采用[[双盲|双盲]]研究。这一论调被{{tsl|en|Union of Concerned Scientists|关切科学家联盟}}批评，该组织批评惠勒的评论“令人窒息地无知”，双盲研究可用作毒品研究，但不适用于环保局的大部分研究，例如测量环境的影响<ref name="UCS">{{Cite web |date=2019-06-06 |title=Wheeler's Breathtaking Ignorance of Science, in One Comment |url=https://blog.ucsusa.org/gretchen-goldman/wheelers-breathtaking-ignorance-of-science-in-one-comment |access-date=2019-06-09 |publisher=Union of Concerned Scientists |language=en-US |archive-date=2020-11-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122011847/https://blog.ucsusa.org/gretchen-goldman/wheelers-breathtaking-ignorance-of-science-in-one-comment |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2019年9月，惠勒签署一项优先减少利用动物做研究，改用{{tsl|en|Alternatives to animal testing|动物实验替代方案|全新替代试验方法}}的指令。这项指令的目标是到2025年将动物实验的请求和资助减少至30%，到2035年淘汰所有哺乳动物研究请求和资助，但部分实验仍然尊周逐案基础批准<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Zaveri |first1=Mihir |last2=Padilla |first2=Mariel |last3=Peiser |first3=Jaclyn |date=2019-09-10 |title=E.P.A. Says It Will Drastically Reduce Animal Testing |work=[[纽约时报|The New York Times]] |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/10/climate/epa-animal-testing.html |access-date=2020-11-06 |publisher=The New York Times |language=en-US |archive-date=2020-08-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200807111536/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/10/climate/epa-animal-testing.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2020年3月，[[2019冠狀病毒病美國疫情|美国爆发2019冠状病毒病疫情]]，环保局宣布无限期停止处罚违反“污染物日常合规检测、廉正测试、取样、实验室分析、培训及报告或认证义务”方面法规的企业，前提是环保局同意疫情促使企业违规。惠勒表示，环保局“承认保护和公众免受2019冠状病毒病威胁所出现的挑战，会直接影响受规管企业迎合所有联邦法规需求的能力”<ref>{{Cite news |last=Friedman |first=Lisa |date=2020-03-26 |title=E.P.A., Citing Coronavirus, Drastically Relaxes Rules for Polluters |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/26/climate/epa-coronavirus-pollution-rules.html |dead-url=no |access-date=2020-05-05 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200327010108/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/26/climate/epa-coronavirus-pollution-rules.html |archive-date=2020-03-27 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last1=Milman |first1=Oliver |last2=Holden |first2=Emily |date=2020-03-27 |title=Trump administration allows companies to break pollution laws during coronavirus pandemic |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/mar/27/trump-pollution-laws-epa-allows-companies-pollute-without-penalty-during-coronavirus |access-date=2020-05-05 |archive-date=2021-01-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105153921/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/mar/27/trump-pollution-laws-epa-allows-companies-pollute-without-penalty-during-coronavirus |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2020年4月，环保局在强制审查会上拒绝提高[[悬浮粒子|悬浮粒子]]（PM 2.5）的处罚环境标准。环保局的科学评估草案估计，当前标准每立方米12毫克每年造成4.5万人死亡，如果将标准提高到每立方米9毫克，会拯救12150人的性命。报告出版后，石油和煤炭公司、汽车和化工生产企业敦促特朗普政府无视这项调查，不收紧政策。惠勒表示，新规草案将悬浮粒子处罚的定量估计权重定得很小<ref>{{Cite news |last=Davenport |first=Coral |date=2020-04-14 |title='Unbelievable' Timing: As Coronavirus Rages, Trump Disregards Advice to Tighten Clean Air Rules |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/14/climate/coronavirus-soot-clean-air-regulations.html |dead-url=no |access-date=2020-05-05 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200414150013/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/14/climate/coronavirus-soot-clean-air-regulations.html |archive-date=2020-04-14 }}</ref>。

惠勒曾计划率团于2020年12日访问台湾，然而《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》批评出访花销巨大，最终导致访问不能成行<ref>{{cite web |last1=A.Dlouhy |first1=Jennfier |title=Trump EPA Chief Scraps Taiwan Visit After Cost Scrutiny |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-11-24/trump-epa-chief-wheeler-scraps-taiwan-visit-after-cost-scrutiny |website=Bloomberg |accessdate=2021-01-17 |date=2020-11-24 |archive-date=2021-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122053415/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-11-24/trump-epa-chief-wheeler-scraps-taiwan-visit-after-cost-scrutiny |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Friedman |first1=Lisa |title=Trump’s E.P.A. Chief Plans 2 Foreign Trips Before Leaving Office |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/19/climate/andrew-wheeler-epa.html |website=The New York Times |accessdate=2021-01-17 |date=2020-11-19 |archive-date=2021-02-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210207091427/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/19/climate/andrew-wheeler-epa.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。12月22日，惠勒与[[中华民国外交部|中华民国外交部]]部长[[吴钊燮|吴钊燮]]通电话<ref>{{cite web |title=吳釗燮與美環保署長惠勒通話 雙方將續深化環保合作 |url=https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/politics/breakingnews/3389095 |website=自由時報電子報 |accessdate=2021-01-17 |date=2020-12-22 |archive-date=2021-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210122045402/https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/politics/breakingnews/3389095 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。若最终成行，惠勒会是继[[美国卫生部|美国卫生部]]部长[[亚历克斯·阿扎|亚历克斯·阿扎]]和{{le|美国经济发展与能源环境次卿|Under Secretary of State for Economic Growth, Energy, and the Environment|经济发展与能源环境次卿}}[[基思·克拉奇|基思·克拉奇]]后，第三位访台的美国高级官员。

同月，环保局削弱{{tsl|en|mercury regulation in the United States|美国汞法规}}效力，大幅度较少未来制定法律时需要考虑的健康利益。惠勒表示，此举是“实在的会计方法”，然而特朗普政府则认为汞净化是必须要做的合适工作<ref>{{Cite news |last=Knickmeyer |first=Ellen |title=EPA guts rule credited with cleaning up coal-plant toxic air |work=Associated Press |url=https://apnews.com/f335db392caae2729636b01910f4055a |access-date=2020-05-05 |archive-date=2020-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201121190052/https://apnews.com/f335db392caae2729636b01910f4055a |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

惠勒未制定任何减少空气污染或碳排放的法规<ref>{{Cite web|title=Wheeler Touts ‘Cost Effective’ EPA But Downplays Bite Of Rollbacks {{!}} InsideEPA.com|url=https://insideepa.com/interview/wheeler-touts-cost-effective-epa-downplays-bite-rollbacks?s=na|access-date=2021-01-15|website=insideepa.com|archive-date=2021-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210115162754/https://insideepa.com/interview/wheeler-touts-cost-effective-epa-downplays-bite-rollbacks?s=na|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===环境观点===
惠勒在《[[法律360|法律360]]》杂志上发表文章<ref name="Baker Daniels" />。2010年，他质疑[[政府間氣候變化專門委員會|政府間氣候變化專門委員會]]的科学严谨性<ref name="EPA">{{Cite web |date=2017-07-25 |title=Reports: Trump to nominate coal lobbyist Wheeler to deputy EPA slot |url=http://www.utilitydive.com/news/reports-trump-to-nominate-coal-lobbyist-wheeler-to-deputy-epa-slot/447795/ |access-date=2017-08-25 |publisher=UtilityDive |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129014554/https://www.utilitydive.com/news/reports-trump-to-nominate-coal-lobbyist-wheeler-to-deputy-epa-slot/447795/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，认为这个组织的定位建基于政治世界观，而非科学事实<ref name="lobbyist" />。在环保局副局长确认听证会上，惠勒被问到是否接受科学界对全球变暖的共识，他答道：“我承认人类有影响气候，但他们没有完全搞懂到底是什么影响<ref name=":4" />。”

2019年3月，惠勒表示不相信气候变化的现存威胁<ref name=":6">{{Cite web |title=EPA: Wheeler on climate: 'I don't see it as the existential threat' |url=https://www.eenews.net/stories/1060123179 |access-date=2019-06-11 |website=www.eenews.net |language=en |archive-date=2020-12-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210195624/https://www.eenews.net/stories/1060123179 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他的这番言论是在针对政府间气候变化专门委员会一份报告的结论，即如果温室气体排放到2030年无法减半，就会有灾难性的后果<ref name=":6" />。

惠勒是国家能源组织（National Energy Resources Organization）的荣休主席<ref>{{Cite web |title=NERO Officers 2015 - 2016 |url=http://nationalenergyresources.com/officers.html |access-date=2017-08-25 |publisher=National Energy Resources Organization |archive-date=2018-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017214132/http://nationalenergyresources.com/officers.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，也是华盛顿煤炭俱乐部（Washington Coal Club）副主席<ref name="Baker Daniels" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-03-18 |title=Coal Lobbyist Could Be Next EPA Deputy Administrator |url=https://www.ecowatch.com/andrew-wheeler-epa-deputy-2318403147.html |access-date=2017-08-25 |publisher=EcoWatch |archive-date=2020-11-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128012956/https://www.ecowatch.com/andrew-wheeler-epa-deputy-2318403147.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

